typedef void(* tpfOtaUpdateCb) (uint8_t u8OtaUpdateStatusType, uint8_t u8OtaUpdateStatus)
 A callback to get OTA status update, the callback provides the status type and its status.
The OTA callback provides the download status, the switch to the downloaded firmware status, roll-back status and Host File Download status. More...

Detailed Description

Specifies the enums and Data Structures used by the OTA APIs.

◆ tpfOtaUpdateCb [5/5]

void(* tpfOtaUpdateCb)(uint8_t u8OtaUpdateStatusType,uint8_t u8OtaUpdateStatus)

A callback to get OTA status update, the callback provides the status type and its status.
The OTA callback provides the download status, the switch to the downloaded firmware status, roll-back status and Host File Download status.

A callback to get OTA status update, the callback provides the download status, the switch to the downloaded firmware status and roll-back status.

Parameters
[in]u8OtaUpdateStatusTypePossible values are listed in tenuOtaUpdateStatusType.
[in]u8OtaUpdateStatusPossible values are listed as enumerated by tenuOtaUpdateStatus.
Note
Executes other callbacks passed to the OTA module.
See also
tenuOtaUpdateStatusType tenuOtaUpdateStatus
Parameters
[in]u8OtaUpdateStatusTypePossible values are listed in tenuOtaUpdateStatusType. Possible types are:
  • DL_STATUS
  • SW_STATUS
  • RB_STATUS
[in]u8OtaUpdateStatusPossible values are listed in tenuOtaUpdateStatus.
See also
tenuOtaUpdateStatusType tenuOtaUpdateStatus

Request to start an OTA update.

M2M_OTA_REQ_SWITCH_FIRMWARE 

Request to switch firmware.

M2M_OTA_REQ_ROLLBACK 

Request to perform an OTA rollback.

M2M_OTA_REQ_ABORT 

Request to abort OTA.

enum tenuM2mOtaCmd

OTA Command IDs.

◆ tenuOtaError [1/12]

enum tenuOtaError
Enumerator
OTA_SUCCESS 

OTA Success status

OTA_ERR_WORKING_IMAGE_LOAD_FAIL 

Failure to load the firmware image

OTA_ERR_INVALID_CONTROL_SEC 

Control structure is corrupted

M2M_ERR_OTA_SWITCH_FAIL 

Switching to the updated image failed as may be the image is invalid

M2M_ERR_OTA_START_UPDATE_FAIL 

OTA update fail due to multiple reasons:

  • Connection failure
  • Image integrity fail
M2M_ERR_OTA_ROLLBACK_FAIL 

Roll-back failed due to Roll-back image is not valid

M2M_ERR_OTA_INVALID_FLASH_SIZE 

The OTA Support at least 4MB flash size, this error code will appear if the current flash is less than 4M

M2M_ERR_OTA_INVALID_ARG 

Ota still in progress

M2M_ERR_OTA_INPROGRESS 

Invalid argument in any OTA Function

  • Connection failure
  • Image integrity fail
